AB  - Recent theoretical work on the determinants of wage-contract length focuses on inflation uncertainty as an explanatory variable additional to the more traditional variable of transactions costs. This paper analyses the empirical determinants of contract duration using a large sample of contract data and confirms the conclusions reached in the theoretical literature.
